[center][size=6][b]Bars Graphics[/b][/size]
[i]Graphics presets and an in-game tuning menu for Schedule I[/i][/center]

[size=5][b]What it is[/b][/size]

Bars Graphics adds a small in-game menu for graphics/performance tuning. It is meant for players who want a few sensible presets first, with Custom settings available when you want to fine tune.

[size=5][b]Features[/b][/size]

[list]
[*]Conservative, Balanced, Aggressive, and Custom profiles
[*]FSR upscaling support, with plain render scale available as a Custom-only fallback
[*]Controls for shadows, LOD, shader detail, texture mip limits, anisotropic filtering, additional lights, camera stacks, terrain foliage, culling, post processing, and frame pacing
[*]F5 in-game menu and F6 optimizer toggle
[*]Staged menu changes: adjust settings first, then press Apply when you are ready
[/list]

[size=5][b]Installation[/b][/size]

Use Vortex/FOMOD, or install manually:

[list]
[*][font=Courier New]Mods/BarsGraphics.dll[/font] -> [font=Courier New]Schedule I/Mods/[/font]
[*][font=Courier New]UserLibs/bGUI.dll[/font] -> [font=Courier New]Schedule I/UserLibs/[/font]
[/list]

[b]Important:[/b] keep [font=Courier New]bGUI.dll[/font] in [font=Courier New]UserLibs[/font]. Do not put it in [font=Courier New]Mods[/font].

[size=5][b]Profiles[/b][/size]

[list]
[*][b]Off[/b]: restores the captured render settings
[*][b]Conservative[/b]: lighter changes, closer to base-game visuals
[*][b]Balanced[/b]: the recommended starting point
[*][b]Aggressive[/b]: stronger FPS-focused tradeoffs
[*][b]Custom[/b]: exposes the same options with short descriptions in the menu
[/list]

[size=5][b]Controls[/b][/size]

[list]
[*][b]F5[/b]: open or close the menu
[*][b]F6[/b]: toggle the optimizer
[*][b]Apply[/b]: save and apply pending menu edits
[*][b]Revert[/b]: discard pending menu edits
[/list]

[size=5][b]Included dependency[/b][/size]

This package includes [font=Courier New]bGUI.dll[/font] in [font=Courier New]UserLibs[/font]. bGUI is MIT licensed; the license text is included in the archive at [font=Courier New]LICENSES/bGUI-MIT.txt[/font].

[size=5][b]Notes[/b][/size]

This is a graphics/performance tuner, not a magic FPS button. Some options have visible tradeoffs. Start with Balanced, check the game in the areas you actually play, then adjust from there.
